   <div id="abbreviationsunderstood-encoding" type="gl-encoding">
      <head>EpiDoc encoding</head>
      <list type="ordered">
         <item id="cos-example"><tag>expan</tag>co<tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>n<tag>/supplied</tag>s<tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>ul<tag>/supplied</tag><tag>/expan</tag></item>
         <item><tag>expan</tag>Aug<tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>ustus<tag>/supplied</tag><tag>/expan</tag></item>
         <item id="augg-example"><tag>expan</tag><tag>abbr</tag>Aug<tag>orig</tag>g<tag>/orig</tag><tag>/abbr</tag><tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>usti duo<tag>/supplied</tag><tag>/expan</tag></item>
         <item id="pr.-example"><tag>expan</tag><tag>abbr</tag>pr<tag>orig</tag><tag>mark type="stop/</tag><tag>/orig</tag><tag>/abbr</tag><tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>esbyter<tag>/supplied</tag><tag>/expan</tag></item>
         <item id="multi-word-example-1"><tag>expan</tag>D<tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>is<tag>/supplied</tag> M<tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>anibus<tag>/supplied</tag><tag>/expan</tag></item>
         <item id="multi-word-example-2"><tag>expan</tag>D<tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>is<tag>/supplied</tag><tag>/expan</tag> <tag>expan</tag>M<tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>anibus<tag>/supplied</tag><tag>/expan</tag></item>
      </list>
      <list type="unordered">
         <head>Notes</head>
        <item>An <tag>abbr</tag> element within the <tag>expan</tag> containing the abbreviated form of the word is available but optional. It may be useful when the abbreviation contains additional markers not in the expanded form (cf. <ref target="augg-example">Augg</ref> and <ref target="pr.-example">pr.</ref> above), but might require additional linking in cases where the abbreviation must be expanded by interpolation (<ref target="cos-example">cf. co(n)s(ul)</ref>)</item>
         <item>When the abbreviated form contains markers not in the expanded form, such as <ref target="augg-example">additional letters</ref> or <ref target="pr.-example">punctuation</ref>, best practice is to put these in <tag>orig</tag> elements, which the standard stylesheets will omit when rendering the expanded form.</item>
      <item>Abbreviated phrases (<abbr expan="for example = exempli gratia">e.g.</abbr>, <foreign lang="lat">D(is) M(anibus)</foreign>) should properly be marked-up as a group, as illustrated in <ref target="multi-word-example-1">the example above</ref>, but marking them as single words is not incorrect (see <ref target="multi-word-example-2">the last example</ref>).</item>
         </list>
   </div>
